Machine learning (ML) is a field that studies the algorithms that improve automatically through experience by extracting generalizable information from data.  Machine learning algorithms build a mathematical model based on sample data, known as &quot;training data&quot;, to make predictions or decisions without being explicitly programmed to do so.   The launch of quantum computing is giving rise to exciting research areas that seek to leverage the principles of quantum mechanics to increase machine learning or vice versa.  The field that uses the Quantum computer has machine learning tools is known as Quantum Machine Learning (QML). Where the goal is to improve classical machine learning algorithms by outsourcing complicated computations to a quantum computer or to optimize quantum algorithms using classical machine learning architectures, both fall within the scope of diversity of machine learning.
